review_title: Volume Control Makes A Difference...ask Nigel Tufnel
review_text:
I purchased this version after my Y-Bot, (an older top heavy version of Mpow Bluetooth FM Transmitter) finally fell and broke for the last time.
Newer versions of this Bluetooth FM Transmitter come without the volume control which is WHY I went with THIS version.
The volume control feature makes a difference in my opinion.
I use this to randomly stream music from both my Amazon Music and Googly Play collections from my phone to my car stereo. The sound quality often varies from track to track, so turning the volume up on the Mpow in conjunction with the volume of the stereo gives an added boost.
The speaker phone option works well, but it's one that I seldom use. I just don't see the need in broadcasting sensitive lab results and other personal drama out into traffic. The overall sound quality of the transmitter is quite good, in fact great even...
...however... since I owned an older version of this transmitter, it's only natural to compare the two.
The volume on this version of transmitter only goes up to 16, whereas the older version went up to 32, which is a seriously noticeable difference, really.
That's the reason why I'm giving this 4 instead of 5 stars. (On  the Tufnel scale the older version went to "11")

review_title: They are very easy to work with and very reasonable on helping if ...
review_text:
I bought my unit from StarTOP. They are very easy to work with and very reasonable on helping if there is a problem with your order or unit. The unit itself is easy to use and I believe to be an accurate reading on the internal temp of cooking meat. I use it with my electric smoker with the extra long lead running through the top vent.  Use this handy setup instead of opening your cooker door to take manual temp readings and thus loosing excess heat and smoke.
The only thing to take note of is this: The food safety agency of the federal government has decided that meat can be cooked to a lower temperature than previously believed and still be safely consumed. Verify and decide this yourself. However the default temps THAT CAN BE MANUALLY ADJUSTED still fall to the formerly recommended higher temps. So regardless you won't go wrong and be unsafe to cook meat hotter than now recommended.
Would buy again. Particularly for the price of this unit. Thanks StarTOP.

review_title: False advertising, fake reviews, SHODDY product! My warning to you!
review_text:
WARNING TO ALL PEOPLE INTERESTED IN THIS, OR SIMILAR ITEMS -- you get what you pay for! All of these small "electronics" companies pay a premium for fake reviews to bump up the star rating on their cheap merchandise made in China (e.g. chargers, battery packs, charging cords, etc.)
Don't buy Samsung's official charger here, either -- I suggest you go directly to their web page, as this site is full of counterfeit devices.
Now to my review:
This charger took up to three and a half (!) hours to charge my galaxy s8 edge from 0 to 100% -- a far cry from the "fast charging" advertised. And three months after the purchase date, the charging discontinues randomly for no reason whatsoever. I have to continuously plug in and re-angle the charging cord in order to resume charging. On several occasions, I have woken up in the morning for work, only to realize that the phone has charged only 10% since the night before.
Here's my advice: ignore the cheap price and buy the REAL DEAL -- and not on amazon, either, go to a real electronics outlet store, or directly to Samsung's website. You will end up spending far less money that way, in the long run.

review_title: Great for the price with a few minor cons
review_text:
Pros:
- Sturdy and well-built.
- Easy pairing.
- Rich and well-balanced sound for the most part.
- Great battery life.
- All around a very good headset for the price!
Cons:
- Poor bass quality in bass-heavy music such as hip hop; otherwise sound is great.
- Annoying ¡®beep¡¯ sound that plays whenever you adjust the volume or play a song.
- My ears start aching after wearing the headphones for 30-45 minutes.
All things considered I can tolerate these drawbacks; this is a very great purchase and well worth the price!

review_title: Works great. Use it with fragrance oils
review_text: Works great. Use it with fragrance oils. Wife loves it. Put's it on in the living room when we come home from work. The fragrance travels throughout the first floor. Last's well over 6 hours if you leave it on continuous mode. It's relatively quite. Unless you add too much water past the line. It'll then gargle a bit as it has to work a little harder to diffuse it. Looks nice with good craftsmanship. The different lights and the transitional effect gives it a nice touch. Will purchase a few for friends and family as gifts.

I purchased this item based on one of your customers reviews which stated that it worked with the Otterbox case. Now you are telling me, after I purchased it that the Otterbox case should be removed. If I have to remove the case before charging it every day, then the unit is more trouble than it is worth.
Update: StarTOP responded to my problem by sending me an upgraded Seneo charger. I have my Galaxy S8+ in an Otterbox Defender case, and the upgraded Seneo works beautifully with my phone in the Otterbox case if I place it on the charger in a horizontal position. I must commend StarTOP for their customer service followup in helping me solve my problem.

review_title: Just absolutely a good a read
review_text: Just absolutely a good a read. Lt. Commander Rorke Denver is brilliant in his perspective and insight he provides throughout his book. His philosophy, wisdom, and how he handles life and what it throws at him is moving and has forever altered my mentality. I love all things Navy SEAL related and enjoyed his experiences but what really moved me is his attitude, love for country and his girls. Highly recommend this book to all.

Had to send this right back -- unit would not charge.  Given recent experiences with this type of vacuum from a couple of manufacturers, I've given up on the whole cordless category.  All vacuums in my house now have cords and I am much happier because of it :)

review_title: Hose is cheap but the vacuum is great.
review_text: The hose is extremely cheap but the vacuum works great picking up small bits of material and thread from the sewing mess I leave.  The filter being washable is a plus.  When it became dirty with lint etc. I just used the lint brush from my sewing machine and it cleaned out fine.  Don't try to unscrew the filter, grab the bar and pull and it comes right out.  I would buy it again.  Shipping was extremely fast.  It works very well without the hose also.  A selling plus for me is that it rechargeable so I don't have to crawl under my work table to plug it in every time I want to use.
Works great! Great sound, connects quickly.

review_title: Super easy to mount, dim-mode makes them useful all night long.
review_text:
These work great for filling in light in places where typical flood lights don't reach. Installing them just takes one screw and a few seconds.
I installed them in areas where my normal house motion lights left a huge shadow. I selected the "dim" always on feature, and the do stay on all light. The motion activation is sensitive enough to allow the lights to come up just when you reach the usable area.
They are also great for installing out near a garden or other places where you don't have any power.

review_title: Great as long as they are away from moving tree limbs
review_text: I have installed these Litom 24 LED lights in three locations around the outside of my house. They really do the job...and never miss human movement. Unfortunately, they also pick up tree movement. I had to move one because a tree limb kept triggering it when the wind blew strong.

review_title: Harbor Digital Kitchen Timer Cooking Timer a good deal!
review_text: This Harbor Digital Kitchen Timer (blue and white) is one of the nicest  timers I have ever purchased. It's appearance is esthetically pleasing, it's just the right size for my hands and has a smooth feel, has a very nice stand for staying upright, the numbers are large and therefore easy to check from a distance, and the volume is quite adequate without being too loud from nearby. The function buttons are very easy to understand and use, and it seems very solid and well-made.  I believe the price was very good for such a useful kitchen timer. I will be ordering a couple more for other applications around our home.
